# Soul Mirror — engineering defaults

## Goals

Ship **less duplicated code** with **clear boundaries**, **security first**, and **automated tests** for every meaningful change.

## Architecture

- **Separate concerns**: `public/api/*.php` (thin) → `App\Application\*` (use cases) → `App\Services\*` (HTTP clients) → `App\Domain\*` (pure helpers). Avoid growing monolith entrypoints.
- **Single responsibility**: One obvious place per behavior (e.g. `AstrologyApiClient`, `KitService`, `ReadingOrchestrator`).
- **Configuration**: Secrets and environment-specific values from `.env` / server environment — never hardcode API keys or tokens in source or HTML.

## Security

- **Validate and constrain inputs** on the server (types, ranges, string length, email shape). Reject bad data with `4xx`, not `5xx`.
- **Do not log PII or secrets** (full emails, API keys, raw tokens). Prefer opaque ids or redaction.
- **Outbound HTTP**: Guzzle with timeouts; handle non-OK responses without leaking upstream bodies to clients.
- **Static + API**: JSON APIs must not expose unsanitized upstream text as error messages to browsers.

## Patterns (maintainability)

- Prefer **composition** over copy-paste; small classes with constructor injection for HTTP clients and config.
- Use **early returns** and small methods to avoid deep nesting.
- When adding features, **extend existing structure** (`src/Services`, `src/Application`) rather than parallel ad-hoc scripts.

## Testing (required habit)

- **New or changed behavior** gets **automated tests** (PHPUnit) — unit tests for pure domain logic; integration tests for HTTP when feasible.
- Run **`composer test`** before considering work done; fix failures before shipping.
- Prefer testing **public behavior** (inputs → outputs, status codes) over private implementation details.

## Frontend (HTML/JS)

- Keep client scripts **minimal**; business rules and secrets stay on the server.
- Avoid inline secrets; use same-origin `/api/...` paths relative to the deployed site root.
